ImaGroupFailureStatus.name: ImaGroupFailureStatus

ImaAlarmStatus.name: ImaAlarmStatus
ImaAlarmStatus.description: A qualification of the IMA trap which indicates if the condition causing the trap has been detected (declared) or is no longer present (cleared).

ImaAlarmType.name: ImaAlarmType
ImaAlarmType.description: An identification of the event that caused the generation of the IMA trap.
ImaAlarmType.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 12.2.3 on page 79

ImaGroupTxClkMode.name: ImaGroupTxClkMode
ImaGroupTxClkMode.description: Indicate the transmit clock mode of the IMA group. There are two possible modes: the Common Transmit Clock (CTC) and the Independent Transmit Clock (ITC). The CTC mode corresponds to the case when the transmit clock of all IMA links are derived from the same source. The ITC configuration corresponds to the case where there is at least one IMA link whose transmit clock is derived from a source different than at least another link transmit clock.
ImaGroupTxClkMode.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 7 on page 38

ImaGroupSymmetry.name: ImaGroupSymmetry
ImaGroupSymmetry.description: The group symmetry mode adjusted during the group start-up.
ImaGroupSymmetry.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 5.2.2.7 on page 35

ImaFrameLength.name: ImaFrameLength
ImaFrameLength.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 5.2.2.4.2 on page 34

ImaLinkState.name: ImaLinkState
ImaLinkState.description: State of a link belonging to an IMA group.

ImaLinkFailureStatus.name: ImaLinkFailureStatus
ImaLinkFailureStatus.description: Local failure status of a link belonging to an IMA group.
ImaLinkFailureStatus.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.1.2 on page 48

ImaTestProcStatus.name: ImaTestProcStatus

imaGroupNumber.name: imaGroupNumber
imaGroupNumber.description: The number of IMA groups configured on this system.

imaGroupEntry.name: imaGroupEntry
imaGroupEntry.description: An entry in the IMA Group table.

imaGroupIndex.name: imaGroupIndex
imaGroupIndex.description: A unique value for the IMA Group.

imaGroupRowStatus.name: imaGroupRowStatus
imaGroupRowStatus.description: The imaGroupRowStatus object allows create, change, and delete operations on imaGroupTable entries. To create a new conceptual row (or instance) of the imaGroupTable, imaGroupRowStatus must be set to 'createAndWait' or 'createAndGo'. If settable, a successful set of the following objects must be performed before the imaGroupRowStatus of a new conceptual row can be set to 'active': imaGroupMinNumTxLinks imaGroupMinNumRxLinks imaGroupTxImaId Some objects in the imaGroupTable control settings which can only be established or changed at group start-up time. These objects include: imaGroupTxImaId imaGroupSymmetry imaGroupTxFrameLength To change (modify) the imaGroupTxImaId object, the manager must first set imaGroupRowStatus to 'notInService'. However, changes to the following two objects can be optionally allowed while the imaGroupRowStatus is 'active': imaGroupSymmetry imaGroupTxFrameLength These two objects can be changed when the imaGroupRowStatus is 'active' in order to allow the far-end to recover from its Config-Aborted state without having to force the near-end Group State machine to go to the 'Not Configured' state. Changing these object values after group start-up has completed causes a restart of the IMA group. Alternatively, as noted above, the agent implementation may simply require the imaGroupRowStatus object to first be set to 'notInService' before allowing changes to either of these two objects. To remove (delete) an imaGroupTable entry from this table, set imaGroupRowStatus to 'destroy'. Setting the imaGroupRowStatus to 'active' has the effect of activating the Group Startup Procedure. The Group Startup Procedure uses provisioned links that have imaLinkRowStatus set to 'active' and imaLinkGroupIndex set to the imaGroupIndex in this conceptual row. When the imaGroupRowStatus is not in 'active' state, the Group State machine is in its 'Not Configured' state.

imaGroupIfIndex.name: imaGroupIfIndex
imaGroupIfIndex.description: This object identifies the logical interface number ('ifIndex') assigned to this IMA group, and is used to identify corresponding rows in the Interfaces MIB. Note that re-initialization of the management agent may cause a client's 'imaGroupIfIndex' to change.

imaGroupNeState.name: imaGroupNeState
imaGroupNeState.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.2.1 on page 55
imaGroupNeState.description: The current operational state of the near-end IMA Group State Machine.

imaGroupFeState.name: imaGroupFeState
imaGroupFeState.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.2.1 on page 55
imaGroupFeState.description: The current operational state of the far-end IMA Group State Machine.

imaGroupFailureStatus.name: imaGroupFailureStatus
imaGroupFailureStatus.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.2.1 on page 55
imaGroupFailureStatus.description: The current failure status of the IMA group (the reason why the GTSM is in the down state).

imaGroupSymmetry.name: imaGroupSymmetry
imaGroupSymmetry.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 5.2.2.7 on page 35

imaGroupMinNumTxLinks.name: imaGroupMinNumTxLinks
imaGroupMinNumTxLinks.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.2.1.1 on page 55
imaGroupMinNumTxLinks.description: Minimum number of transmit links required to be Active for the IMA group to be in the Operational state.

imaGroupMinNumRxLinks.name: imaGroupMinNumRxLinks
imaGroupMinNumRxLinks.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.2.1.1 on page 55
imaGroupMinNumRxLinks.description: Minimum number of receive links required to be Active for the IMA group to be in the Operational state.

imaGroupNeTxClkMode.name: imaGroupNeTxClkMode
imaGroupNeTxClkMode.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 7 on page 38
imaGroupNeTxClkMode.description: Transmit clocking mode used by the near-end IMA group.

imaGroupFeTxClkMode.name: imaGroupFeTxClkMode
imaGroupFeTxClkMode.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 7 on page 38
imaGroupFeTxClkMode.description: Transmit clocking mode used by the far-end IMA group.

imaGroupTxTimingRefLink.name: imaGroupTxTimingRefLink
imaGroupTxTimingRefLink.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 8.1.1 on page 41
imaGroupTxTimingRefLink.description: The ifIndex of the transmit timing reference link to be used by the near-end for IMA data cell clock recovery from the ATM layer. The distinguished value of zero may be used if no link has been configured in the IMA group, or if the transmit timing reference link has not yet been selected.

imaGroupRxTimingRefLink.name: imaGroupRxTimingRefLink
imaGroupRxTimingRefLink.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 8.1.1 on page 41
imaGroupRxTimingRefLink.description: The ifIndex of the receive timing reference link to be used by near-end for IMA data cell clock recovery toward the ATM layer. The distinguished value of zero may be used if no link has been configured in the IMA group, or if the receive timing reference link has not yet been detected.

imaGroupLastChange.name: imaGroupLastChange
imaGroupLastChange.description: The time-of-day the IMA group last changed operational state (i.e., value of imaGroupNeState changed).

imaGroupTxImaId.name: imaGroupTxImaId
imaGroupTxImaId.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 5.2.2.6 on page 35
imaGroupTxImaId.description: The IMA ID currently in use by the near-end IMA function.

imaGroupRxImaId.name: imaGroupRxImaId
imaGroupRxImaId.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 5.2.2.6 on page 35
imaGroupRxImaId.description: The IMA ID currently in use by the far-end IMA function.

imaGroupTxFrameLength.name: imaGroupTxFrameLength
imaGroupTxFrameLength.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 5.2.2.4.2 on page 34
imaGroupTxFrameLength.description: The frame length to be used by the IMA group in the transmit direction. Can only be set when the IMA group is startup.

imaGroupRxFrameLength.name: imaGroupRxFrameLength
imaGroupRxFrameLength.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 5.2.2.4.2 on page 34
imaGroupRxFrameLength.description: Value of IMA frame length as received from remote IMA function.

imaGroupDiffDelayMax.name: imaGroupDiffDelayMax
imaGroupDiffDelayMax.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 9.2 on page 45
imaGroupDiffDelayMax.description: The maximum number of milliseconds of differential delay among the links that will be tolerated on this interface.

imaGroupLeastDelayLink.name: imaGroupLeastDelayLink
imaGroupLeastDelayLink.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 9.2 on page 45
imaGroupLeastDelayLink.description: The ifIndex of the link configured in the IMA group which has the smallest link propagation delay. The distinguished value of zero may be used if no link has been configured in the IMA group, or if the link with the smallest link propagation delay has not yet been determined.

imaGroupDiffDelayMaxObs.name: imaGroupDiffDelayMaxObs
imaGroupDiffDelayMaxObs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 9.2 on page 45
imaGroupDiffDelayMaxObs.description: The latest maximum differential delay observed (in milliseconds) between the links having the least and most link propagation delay, among the receive links that are currently configured in the IMA group.

imaGroupAlphaValue.name: imaGroupAlphaValue
imaGroupAlphaValue.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 11 on page 68
imaGroupAlphaValue.description: This indicates the 'alpha' value used to specify the number of consecutive invalid ICP cells to be detected before moving to the IMA Hunt state from the IMA Sync state.

imaGroupBetaValue.name: imaGroupBetaValue
imaGroupBetaValue.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 11 on page 68
imaGroupBetaValue.description: This indicates the 'beta' value used to specify the number of consecutive errored ICP cells to be detected before moving to the IMA Hunt state from the IMA Sync state.

imaGroupGammaValue.name: imaGroupGammaValue
imaGroupGammaValue.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 11 on page 68
imaGroupGammaValue.description: This indicates the 'gamma' value used to specify the number of consecutive valid ICP cells to be detected before moving to the IMA Sync state from the IMA PreSync state.

imaGroupRunningSecs.name: imaGroupRunningSecs
imaGroupRunningSecs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.2.1 on page 55
imaGroupRunningSecs.description: The amount of time (in seconds) since this IMA group has been in the Operational state.

imaGroupUnavailSecs.name: imaGroupUnavailSecs
imaGroupUnavailSecs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.2.1 on page 55 and (R-136) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaGroupUnavailSecs.description: Count of one second intervals where the IMA Group Traffic State Machine is Down.

imaGroupNeNumFailures.name: imaGroupNeNumFailures
imaGroupNeNumFailures.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (R-137) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaGroupNeNumFailures.description: The number of times a near-end group failure (Config-Aborted, Insufficient-Links) has been reported since power-up or reboot.

imaGroupFeNumFailures.name: imaGroupFeNumFailures
imaGroupFeNumFailures.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (O-25) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaGroupFeNumFailures.description: The number of times a far-end group failure (Config-Aborted-FE, Insufficient-Links-FE, Blocked-FE) has been reported since power-up or reboot. This is an optional attribute.

imaGroupTxAvailCellRate.name: imaGroupTxAvailCellRate
imaGroupTxAvailCellRate.description: The current cell rate (truncated value in cells per second) provided by this IMA group in the transmit direction, considering all the transmit links in the Active state.

imaGroupRxAvailCellRate.name: imaGroupRxAvailCellRate
imaGroupRxAvailCellRate.description: The current cell rate (truncated value in cells per second) provided by this IMA group in the receive direction, considering all the receive links in the Active state.

imaGroupNumTxCfgLinks.name: imaGroupNumTxCfgLinks
imaGroupNumTxCfgLinks.description: The number of links that are configured to transmit in this IMA group. This attribute overwrites the value of the imaGroupNumRxActLinks attribute when the IMA group is configured in the Symmetrical Configuration group symmetry mode.

imaGroupNumRxCfgLinks.name: imaGroupNumRxCfgLinks
imaGroupNumRxCfgLinks.description: The number of links that are configured to receive in this IMA group. This attribute is overwritten by the value of the imaGroupNumTxActLinks attribute when the IMA group is configured in the Symmetrical Configuration group symmetry mode.

imaGroupNumTxActLinks.name: imaGroupNumTxActLinks
imaGroupNumTxActLinks.description: The number of links which are configured to transmit and are currently Active in this IMA group.

imaGroupNumRxActLinks.name: imaGroupNumRxActLinks
imaGroupNumRxActLinks.description: The number of links which are configured to receive and are currently Active in this IMA group.

imaGroupTestLinkIfIndex.name: imaGroupTestLinkIfIndex
imaGroupTestLinkIfIndex.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 13 on page 81
imaGroupTestLinkIfIndex.description: This object is used to designate an interface as the test link for use in the Test Pattern Procedure. The distinguished value of zero specifies that the implementation may choose the Test Link, in which case, the implementation may also choose the value of 'imaGroupTestPattern'. The value zero may also be used if no link has yet been added to the group. Note that this value is NOT the same as the Tx LID value, but instead either identifies the ifIndex value of the test link to be used by the Test Pattern Procedure (i.e., the link whose LID value is inserted in the Tx LID field of the transmitted ICP cells), or identifies that the implementation may choose the test link (if the value is zero).

imaGroupTestPattern.name: imaGroupTestPattern
imaGroupTestPattern.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 13 on page 81
imaGroupTestPattern.description: The value of this object is used to specify the Tx Test Pattern in an IMA group loopback operation. A value in the range 0 to 255 designates a specific pattern. The distinguished value of -1 specifies that the implementation may choose the value. In this case, the implementation may also choose the value of 'imaGroupTestLinkIfIndex'. It is recommended that the specific value 255 not be used for testing, since by (R-137) the IMA interface is required to transmit 0xFF (i.e., 255) when the incoming test command is inactive or the test link is not detected, and thus it cannot be established for certain whether 255 was received due to an actual loopback operation or due to the normal operation of an IMA that is not performing (or else cannot perform) the test pattern procedure.

imaGroupTestProcStatus.name: imaGroupTestProcStatus
imaGroupTestProcStatus.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 13 on page 81
imaGroupTestProcStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the Test Pattern Procedure, and to note whether at least one link failed the test. The test is started by setting operating(2) status. If any link should fail the test, the IMA will set the status to linkFail(3). The linkFail(3) state will persist until either the disabled(1) state is set or until no instance of imaLinkTestProcStatus has the value linkFail(3). Only the values disabled(1) and operating(2) may be written. Writing the operating(2) value will not cause clearing of the linkFail(3) state.

imaGroupValidIntervals.name: imaGroupValidIntervals
imaGroupValidIntervals.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (O-26) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaGroupValidIntervals.description: The number of previous 15 minute intervals for which valid data was collected. The value will be 96 unless the IMA group table entry was created within the last 24 hours, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals since the IMA group table entry was created. In the case where the agent is a proxy, it is possible that some intervals are unavailable. In this case, this value is the maximum interval number for which valid data is available. This attribute is only mandatory when the IMA Group Interval Statistics and/or IMA Group Total Statistics objects are implemented.

imaGroupInvalidIntervals.name: imaGroupInvalidIntervals
imaGroupInvalidIntervals.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (O-26) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaGroupInvalidIntervals.description: The number of intervals for which no valid data is available. This attribute is only mandatory when the IMA Group Interval Statistics and/or IMA Group Total Statistics objects are implemented.

imaGroupTimeElapsed.name: imaGroupTimeElapsed
imaGroupTimeElapsed.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (O-26) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaGroupTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current measurement period. This attribute is only mandatory when the IMA Group Current Statistics are implemented.

imaGroupTxOamLabelValue.name: imaGroupTxOamLabelValue
imaGroupTxOamLabelValue.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 5.2.2.3 on page 32
imaGroupTxOamLabelValue.description: IMA OAM Label value transmitted by the NE IMA unit.

imaGroupRxOamLabelValue.name: imaGroupRxOamLabelValue
imaGroupRxOamLabelValue.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 5.2.2.3 on page 32
imaGroupRxOamLabelValue.description: IMA OAM Label value transmitted by the FE IMA unit. The value 0 likely means that the IMA unit has not received an OAM Label from the FE IMA unit at this time.

imaGroupMappingTable.name: imaGroupMappingTable
imaGroupMappingTable.description: A table mapping the 'ifIndex' values of 'imaGroupIfIndex' to the 'imaGroupIndex' values of the corresponding IMA group.

imaGroupMappingEntry.name: imaGroupMappingEntry
imaGroupMappingEntry.description: Each row describes one ifIndex to imaGroupIndex mapping.

imaGroupMappingIndex.name: imaGroupMappingIndex
imaGroupMappingIndex.description: The imaGroupIndex of the IMA Group which implements the specified interface.

imaLinkTable.name: imaLinkTable
imaLinkTable.description: The IMA group Link Status and Configuration table.

imaLinkEntry.name: imaLinkEntry
imaLinkEntry.description: An entry in the IMA Group Link table.

imaLinkIfIndex.name: imaLinkIfIndex
imaLinkIfIndex.description: This corresponds to the 'ifIndex' of the MIB-II interface on which this link is established. This object also corresponds to the logical number ('ifIndex') assigned to this IMA link.

imaLinkRowStatus.name: imaLinkRowStatus
imaLinkRowStatus.description: The imaLinkRowStatus object allows create, change, and delete operations on imaLinkTable entries. To create a new conceptual row (or instance) of the imaLinkTable, imaLinkRowStatus must be set to 'createAndWait' or 'createAndGo'. A successful set of the imaLinkGroupIndex object must be performed before the imaLinkRowStatus of a new conceptual row can be set to 'active'. To change (modify) the imaLinkGroupIndex in an imaLinkTable entry, the imaLinkRowStatus object must first be set to 'notInService'. Only then can this object in the conceptual row be modified. This is due to the fact that the imaLinkGroupIndex object provides the association between a physical IMA link and the IMA group to which it belongs, and setting the imaLinkGroupIndex object to a different value has the effect of changing the association between a physical IMA link and an IMA group. To place the link 'in group', the imaLinkRowStatus object is set to 'active'. While the row is not in 'active' state, both the Transmit and Receive IMA link state machines are in the 'Not In Group' state. To remove (delete) an imaLinkTable entry from this table, set this object to 'destroy'.

imaLinkGroupIndex.name: imaLinkGroupIndex
imaLinkGroupIndex.description: The value which identifies the IMA group (imaGroupIndex) of which this link is a member.

imaLinkNeTxState.name: imaLinkNeTxState
imaLinkNeTxState.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.1.2 on page 48
imaLinkNeTxState.description: The current state of the near-end transmit link.

imaLinkNeRxState.name: imaLinkNeRxState
imaLinkNeRxState.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.1.2 on page 48
imaLinkNeRxState.description: The current state of the near-end receive link.

imaLinkFeTxState.name: imaLinkFeTxState
imaLinkFeTxState.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.1.2 on page 48
imaLinkFeTxState.description: The current state of the far-end transmit link as reported via ICP cells.

imaLinkFeRxState.name: imaLinkFeRxState
imaLinkFeRxState.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.1.2 on page 48
imaLinkFeRxState.description: The current state of the far-end receive link as reported via ICP cells.

imaLinkNeRxFailureStatus.name: imaLinkNeRxFailureStatus
imaLinkNeRxFailureStatus.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.1.2 on page 48
imaLinkNeRxFailureStatus.description: The current link failure status of the near-end receive link.

imaLinkFeRxFailureStatus.name: imaLinkFeRxFailureStatus
imaLinkFeRxFailureStatus.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 10.1.2 on page 48
imaLinkFeRxFailureStatus.description: The current link failure status of the far-end receive link as reported via ICP cells.

imaLinkTxLid.name: imaLinkTxLid
imaLinkTxLid.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 5.2.2.1 on page 26
imaLinkTxLid.description: The outgoing LID used currently on the link by the local end. This value has meaning only if the link belongs to an IMA group.

imaLinkRxLid.name: imaLinkRxLid
imaLinkRxLid.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 5.2.2.1 on page 26
imaLinkRxLid.description: The incoming LID used currently on the link by the remote end as reported via ICP cells. This value has meaning only if the link belongs to an IMA group.

imaLinkRelDelay.name: imaLinkRelDelay
imaLinkRelDelay.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 9.2 on page 45
imaLinkRelDelay.description: The latest measured delay on this link relative to the link, in the same IMA group, with the least delay.

imaLinkImaViolations.name: imaLinkImaViolations
imaLinkImaViolations.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (R-125) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkImaViolations.description: ICP violations: count of errored, invalid or missing ICP cells, except during SES-IMA or UAS-IMA conditions.

imaLinkOifAnomalies.name: imaLinkOifAnomalies
imaLinkOifAnomalies.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (O-20) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkOifAnomalies.description: The number of OIF anomalies, except during SES-IMA or UAS-IMA conditions, at the near-end. This is an optional attribute.

imaLinkNeSevErroredSecs.name: imaLinkNeSevErroredSecs
imaLinkNeSevErroredSecs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (R-126) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkNeSevErroredSecs.description: Count of one second intervals containing >= 30% of the ICP cells counted as IV-IMAs, or one or more link defects (e.g., LOS, OOF/LOF, AIS, or LCD), LIF defects, or LODS defects, except during UAS-IMA condition.

imaLinkFeSevErroredSecs.name: imaLinkFeSevErroredSecs
imaLinkFeSevErroredSecs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (R-127) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkFeSevErroredSecs.description: Count of one second intervals containing one or more RDI-IMA defects, except during UAS-IMA-FE condition.

imaLinkNeUnavailSecs.name: imaLinkNeUnavailSecs
imaLinkNeUnavailSecs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (R-128) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkNeUnavailSecs.description: Count of unavailable seconds at near-end: unavailability begins at the onset of 10 contiguous SES-IMA and ends at the onset of 10 contiguous seconds with no SES-IMA.

imaLinkFeUnavailSecs.name: imaLinkFeUnavailSecs
imaLinkFeUnavailSecs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (R-129) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkFeUnavailSecs.description: Count of unavailable seconds at far-end: unavailability begins at the onset of 10 contiguous SES-IMA-FE and ends at the onset of 10 contiguous seconds with no SES-IMA-FE.

imaLinkNeTxUnusableSecs.name: imaLinkNeTxUnusableSecs
imaLinkNeTxUnusableSecs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (R-130) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkNeTxUnusableSecs.description: Tx Unusable seconds: count of Tx Unusable seconds at the near-end Tx LSM.

imaLinkNeRxUnusableSecs.name: imaLinkNeRxUnusableSecs
imaLinkNeRxUnusableSecs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (R-131) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkNeRxUnusableSecs.description: Rx Unusable seconds: count of Rx Unusable seconds at the near-end Rx LSM.

imaLinkFeTxUnusableSecs.name: imaLinkFeTxUnusableSecs
imaLinkFeTxUnusableSecs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (R-132) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkFeTxUnusableSecs.description: Tx Unusable seconds at far-end: count of seconds with Tx Unusable indications from the far-end Tx LSM.

imaLinkFeRxUnusableSecs.name: imaLinkFeRxUnusableSecs
imaLinkFeRxUnusableSecs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (R-133) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkFeRxUnusableSecs.description: Rx Unusable seconds at far-end: count of seconds with Rx Unusable indications from the far-end Rx LSM.

imaLinkNeTxNumFailures.name: imaLinkNeTxNumFailures
imaLinkNeTxNumFailures.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (R-134) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkNeTxNumFailures.description: The number of times a near-end transmit failure alarm condition has been entered on this link (i.e., some form of implementation specific transmit fault).

imaLinkNeRxNumFailures.name: imaLinkNeRxNumFailures
imaLinkNeRxNumFailures.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (R-135) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkNeRxNumFailures.description: The number of times a near-end receive failure alarm condition has been entered on this link (i.e., LIF, LODS, RFI-IMA, Mis-Connected or some form of implementation specific receive fault).

imaLinkFeTxNumFailures.name: imaLinkFeTxNumFailures
imaLinkFeTxNumFailures.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (O-21) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkFeTxNumFailures.description: The number of times a far-end transmit failure alarm condition has been entered on this link (i.e., Tx-Unusable-FE). This is an optional attribute.

imaLinkFeRxNumFailures.name: imaLinkFeRxNumFailures
imaLinkFeRxNumFailures.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (O-22) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkFeRxNumFailures.description: The number of times a far-end receive failure alarm condition has been entered on this link (i.e., Rx-Unusable-FE). This is an optional attribute.

imaLinkTxStuffs.name: imaLinkTxStuffs
imaLinkTxStuffs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (O-23) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkTxStuffs.description: Count of stuff events inserted in the transmit direction. This is an optional attribute.

imaLinkRxStuffs.name: imaLinkRxStuffs
imaLinkRxStuffs.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (O-24) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkRxStuffs.description: Count of stuff events detected in the receive direction. This is an optional attribute.

imaLinkRxTestPattern.name: imaLinkRxTestPattern
imaLinkRxTestPattern.description: This object identifies the test pattern received in the ICP Cell (octet 17) on the link during the IMA Test Pattern Procedure. This value may then be compared to the transmitted test pattern.

imaLinkTestProcStatus.name: imaLinkTestProcStatus
imaLinkTestProcStatus.description: This value indicates the current state of the Test Pattern Procedure. If the value is disabled(1), the test is not running. A value of operating(2) means the test is running and no error has been found on this interface. A value of linkFail(3) means an error has been detected on this link during the test. Once an error is detected, the linkFail(3) value is latched until either this object is read or until the imaGroupTestProcStatus is moved to disabled(1). Once read, if the error no longer persists, a subsequent read will report the value operating(2).

imaLinkValidIntervals.name: imaLinkValidIntervals
imaLinkValidIntervals.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (O-26) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkValidIntervals.description: The number of previous 15 minute intervals for which valid data was collected. The value will be 96 unless the IMA group table entry was created within the last 24 hours, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals since the IMA group table entry was created. In the case where the agent is a proxy, it is possible that some intervals are unavailable. In this case, this value is the maximum interval number for which valid data is available. This attribute is only mandatory when the IMA Link Interval Statistics and/or IMA Link Total Statistics objects are implemented.

imaLinkInvalidIntervals.name: imaLinkInvalidIntervals
imaLinkInvalidIntervals.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (O-26) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkInvalidIntervals.description: The number of intervals for which no valid data is available. This attribute is only mandatory when the IMA Link Interval Statistics and/or IMA Link Total Statistics objects are implemented.

imaLinkTimeElapsed.name: imaLinkTimeElapsed
imaLinkTimeElapsed.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, (O-26) in Section 12.2.2.2 on page 77
imaLinkTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current measurement period. This attribute is only mandatory when the IMA Link Current Statistics are implemented.

imaAlarmType.name: imaAlarmType
imaAlarmType.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 12.2.3 on page 79
imaAlarmType.description: The Type of IMA alarm declared or cleared. The value of ImaAlarmType identifies the type of alarm according to the definitions in the IMA specification.

imaFailureAlarm.name: imaFailureAlarm
imaFailureAlarm.description: The imaFailureAlarm provides a method for an agent implementing IMA to notify an NMS of an alarm condition.
imaFailureAlarm.reference: ATM Forum IMA v1.1, Section 12.2.3 on page 79
